    • getNodeMapIndex

      public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer> getNodeMapIndex()

      Returns a mapping of the program's workload's nodes to an index.

      A Hashmap is returned that maps a Node to an index number. The lower the number, the further to the front of the alphabet the node is.

      Returns:
      nodeIndexMap from Strings representing node names to Integers for their alphabetical order
